# Cursor Rules for Near Era Cleexe

## Project Overview
- **Project**: Near Era Cleexe Mobile App
- **Type**: React + TypeScript + Vite
- **Target**: Mobile-first responsive web application

## Architecture Rules

### 1. Project Structure
- Use the existing folder structure strictly: `/src` contains all source code
- Keep components in `/src/components` (each component in its own folder)
- Keep pages in `/src/pages` (each page in its own folder)
- Server logic/services in `/src/services`
- Reusable functions in `/src/utils`
- Type definitions in `/src/types`
- Global styles in `/src/styles`
- Configuration in `/src/config`
- Custom hooks in `/src/hooks`
- Context/state management in `/src/context`

### 2. Component Rules
- Use functional components with hooks
- One component per file
- Include component CSS in same directory (Component.tsx + Component.css)
- Export component as default
- Add TypeScript types for all props
- Use path aliases (@types, @components, etc)

### 3. TypeScript Rules
- STRICT mode enabled - no `any` types
- All functions must have type annotations
- All component props must be typed
- Use interfaces for object types
- Export types from `/src/types/index.ts`

### 4. Styling Rules
- Use CSS modules or plain CSS
- Follow mobile-first responsive design (@media queries)
- Use CSS variables for theming when possible
- Color scheme: Purple gradients (#667eea, #764ba2)
- Maintain consistent padding/margins

### 5. API Integration
- Use axios via `/src/services/api.ts`
- All API calls in service files
- Handle errors consistently
- Use custom error classes from `/src/utils/errors.ts`

### 6. State Management
- Use React Context for global state
- Use useLocalStorage hook for persistent data
- Props drilling for local component state
- Avoid prop drilling with context when needed

### 7. Code Style
- ESLint + Prettier configured
- 2-space indentation
- Semicolons required
- Single quotes for strings
- Max line width: 100 characters
- Always format code before committing

### 8. File Naming
- Components: PascalCase (Button.tsx)
- Utils/services/hooks: camelCase (logger.ts)
- Types: interfaces with capital first letter
- CSS files: match component name (Button.css)

### 9. Import Rules
- Use path aliases (@ imports)
- Organize imports: React first, then libraries, then local
- Use named exports for utilities
- Use default export for components

### 10. Environment Variables
- All env vars prefixed with VITE_
- Define in .env.example and .env
- Access via `import.meta.env.VITE_*`
- Never commit .env file

## Git Workflow
- Branch naming: feature/\*, bugfix/\*, hotfix/\*
- Commit messages: clear and descriptive
- Keep commits atomic
- Push to feature branches before PR

## Common Commands
```bash
npm run dev          # Start dev server
npm run build        # Build for production
npm run lint         # Check code quality
npm run format       # Format code with Prettier
npm run type-check   # Check TypeScript
```

## Important Notes
- Maintain mobile-first approach in all designs
- Always test responsive behavior
- Keep bundle size minimal
- Use lazy loading for routes when needed
- Document complex logic with comments
- Follow the established patterns in existing code
